.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-ALERT 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.7.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-alert \- alert export, import, planning, apply, routing, and authoring workflows
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util alert [\fISUBCOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Run the alerting command surface for exporting, importing, diffing, planning, applying, deleting, authoring, and listing Grafana alert resources.
.IP \(bu 2
Export local alert bundles from Grafana.
.IP \(bu 2
Import or diff alert bundles against live Grafana state.
.IP \(bu 2
Build and apply a reviewed alert management plan.
.IP \(bu 2
Author staged rules, contact points, routes, and templates.
.IP \(bu 2
List live alert rules, contact points, mute timings, and templates.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B export
Export alerting resources into raw/ JSON files.
.TP
.B import
Import alerting resource JSON files through the Grafana API.
.TP
.B diff
Compare local alerting export files against live Grafana resources.
.TP
.B plan
Build a staged alert management plan from desired alert resources.
.TP
.B apply
Apply a reviewed alert management plan.
.TP
.B delete
Delete one explicit alert resource identity.
.TP
.B add\-rule
Author a staged alert rule from the higher\-level authoring surface.
.TP
.B clone\-rule
Clone an existing staged alert rule into a new authoring target.
.TP
.B add\-contact\-point
Author a staged alert contact point from the higher\-level authoring surface.
.TP
.B set\-route
Author or replace the tool\-owned staged notification route.
.TP
.B preview\-route
Preview the managed route inputs without changing runtime behavior.
.TP
.B new\-rule
Create a low\-level staged alert rule scaffold.
.TP
.B new\-contact\-point
Create a low\-level staged alert contact point scaffold.
.TP
.B new\-template
Create a low\-level staged alert template scaffold.
.TP
.B list\-rules
List live Grafana alert rules.
.TP
.B list\-contact\-points
List live Grafana alert contact points.
.TP
.B list\-mute\-timings
List live Grafana mute timings.
.TP
.B list\-templates
List live Grafana notification templates.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.IP \(bu 2
\-\-profile, \-\-url, \-\-token, \-\-basic\-user, \-\-basic\-password
.IP \(bu 2
\-\-prompt\-password, \-\-prompt\-token, \-\-timeout, \-\-verify\-ssl
.IP \(bu 2
Use the nested subcommands for export, import, diff, plan, apply, delete, add\-rule, clone\-rule, add\-contact\-point, set\-route, preview\-route, new\-rule, new\-contact\-point, new\-template, list\-rules, list\-contact\-points, list\-mute\-timings, and list\-templates.
.SH WORKFLOW NOTES
.PP
The safest alert workflow is: author or update desired files, inspect the delta with alert plan, then execute only reviewed changes with alert apply.
.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
grafana-util alert list-rules --profile prod --json
.EE
.EX
grafana-util alert export --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin --output-dir ./alerts --overwrite
.EE
.EX
grafana-util alert export --url http://localhost:3000 --token "$GRAFANA_API_TOKEN" --output-dir ./alerts --flat
.EE
.EX
grafana-util alert export --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin --output-dir ./alerts --flat
.EE
.EX
grafana-util alert import --url http://localhost:3000 --import-dir ./alerts/raw --replace-existing
.EE
.EX
grafana-util alert import --url http://localhost:3000 --import-dir ./alerts/raw --replace-existing --dry-run --json
.EE
